/***** Global Balloon Design -- START *****/
/* Title text */
.walkme-custom-balloon-title{
	font-family: "Helvetica Neue","Arial","Helvetica","Verdana",sans-serif !important;
	color: #000 !important;
	font-size: 18px !important;
	line-height: 1em !important;
	margin: 0px 8px 0px 8px !important;
	padding: 18px 18px 9px 8px !important;
	font-weight: bold !important;
	border-bottom: 1px solid #DBDBDB !important;
}
/* Content text */
.walkme-custom-balloon-content{
	font-family: "Cambria","Georgia",serif !important;
	color: #000 !important;
	font-size: 15px !important;
	line-height: 1.4em !important;
	padding: 18px 16px 16px 16px !important;
	margin: 0px !important;
}
/* Styling balloons with no buttons */
.walkme-custom-no-buttons .walkme-custom-balloon-title{
	border-bottom: none !important;
}
.walkme-custom-no-buttons .walkme-custom-balloon-buttons-wrapper{
	height: auto !important;
}
/* Disable side border & seperator */
.walkme-custom-side-border,
.walkme-custom-balloon-separator{
	display: none !important;
}
/* Centering buttons */
.walkme-custom-balloon-buttons-wrapper{
	text-align: center !important;
	height: 43px !important;
}
/* Remove back button */
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-weak-button.walkme-custom-balloon-back-button.walkme-action-back{
	display: none !important;
}
/* Next/Done Button styling */
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-next-button.walkme-action-next,
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-done-button.walkme-action-done{	
	height: 25px !important;
	margin-bottom: 18px !important;
	margin-top: 0px !important;
	background: -moz-linear-gradient(#FFF, #E5E5E5) !important;
	background: -webkit-linear-gradient(#FFF, #E5E5E5) !important;
	background: -o-linear-gradient(#FFF, #E5E5E5) !important;
	background: linear-gradient(#FFF, #E5E5E5) !important;
	background-color: #E5E5E5 !important;
	border: 1px solid #CCC !important;
}
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-next-button.walkme-action-next .walkme-custom-balloon-button-text,
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-done-button.walkme-action-done .walkme-custom-balloon-button-text{
	font-family: "Helvetica Neue","Arial","Helvetica","Verdana",sans-serif !important;
	font-size: 12px !important;
	font-weight: 600 !important;
	color: #000 !important;
}
/* Next/Done Button - Hover state */
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-next-button.walkme-action-next:hover,
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-done-button.walkme-action-done:hover{
	background: -moz-linear-gradient(#FFF, #F2F2F2) !important;
	background: -webkit-linear-gradient(#FFF, #F2F2F2) !important;
	background: -o-linear-gradient(#FFF, #F2F2F2) !important;
	background: linear-gradient(#FFF, #F2F2F2) !important;
	background-color: #F2F2F2 !important;
}
/* Next/Done Button - Active state */
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-next-button.walkme-action-next:active,
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-done-button.walkme-action-done:active{
	background: -moz-linear-gradient(#FEFEFE, #EBEBEB) !important;
	background: -webkit-linear-gradient(#FEFEFE, #EBEBEB) !important;
	background: -o-linear-gradient(#FEFEFE, #EBEBEB) !important;
	background: linear-gradient(#FEFEFE, #EBEBEB) !important;
	background-color: #EBEBEB !important;
	box-shadow: 4px 4px 10px 0px #CCC inset !important;
}
/* Next/Done Button - Tab focus state */
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-next-button.walkme-action-next:focus,
.walkme-custom-balloon-button.walkme-custom-balloon-normal-button.walkme-custom-balloon-done-button.walkme-action-done:focus{
	bottom: 2px solid #000 !important;
}
/* Close 'X' Icon */
.walkme-click-and-hover.walkme-action-close{
	font-size: 1px !important;
  color: transparent !important;
}
.walkme-click-and-hover.walkme-action-close::before{
	content: "" !important;
	position: absolute !important;
	background: url("https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/walkme.external/customers/FidelityExternal/X_icon15.png") !important;
	background-repeat: no-repeat !important;
	background-position: center !important;
	width: 15px !important;
	height: 15px !important;
	margin: 8px !important;
	right: 0px !important;
	top: 0px !important;
}
/* Custom BBCode Links */
.walkme-custom-bbcode-link{
	font-family: "Cambria","Georgia",serif !important;
	color: #0F57C2 !important;
	font-size: 15px !important;
	line-height: 1.4em !important;
	text-decoration: none !important;
}
.walkme-custom-bbcode-link:hover{
	cursor: pointer !important;
	text-decoration: underline !important;
}
.walkme-custom-bbcode-link:visited{
	color: #800080 !important;
	text-decoration: none !important;
}
.walkme-custom-bbcode-link:active,
.walkme-custom-bbcode-link:focus{
	color: #E74600 !important;
	text-decoration: underline !important;
}
/* Border */
.walkme-custom-balloon-inner-div{
	border: 2px #999 solid !important;
}
.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-outer{
	color: #999 !important;
}
/* Removing seperator for Title only or Content only balloons */
.walkme-custom-no-content .walkme-custom-balloon-title{
	border-bottom: 0px !important;
	padding-bottom: 16px !important;
}
.walkme-custom-no-title .walkme-custom-balloon-title{
	display: none !important;
}
/* Adjusting padding for content only balloons */
.walkme-custom-no-title .walkme-custom-balloon-content{
	padding-top: 26px !important;
}
/* Left arrow fix */
.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-inner.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-right{
	border-color: transparent #FFFFFF transparent currentcolor !important;
}
.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-outer.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-right{	
	border-color: transparent #999 transparent currentcolor !important;
}
/* Bottom arrow fix */
.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-top.walkme-custom-balloon-arrow-inner{
	border-color: #FFFFFF transparent !important;
}
/***** Global Balloon Design -- END *****/

</div>
					<div id="legal-footer--performance" class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" style="display: none;">
						<p>Personal Rate of Return information for authorized Fidelity accounts will become available the monthly cycle following authorization. For periods less than one year, performance returns are presented on a cumulative basis.</p>
						<p>If your return information contains dashes '--', we either don't have a return for that time period, or your account is being validated. Accounts opened after the beginning of the year are excluded from the calculation.</p>
						<p>Your Personal Rate of Return is calculated using a money-weighted formula. It reflects the performance of the underlying investments in your eligible Fidelity accounts including dividends, interest, and fees; as well as the size and timing of your individual trades. If you use an account with cash management features, the Personal Rate of Return calculation may be affected by deposits, withdrawals, bill payment and other money movement transactions. Non-Fidelity accounts are excluded from the calculation. The Personal Rate of Return is an estimate only and should not be used solely in making investment decisions. It is calculated using Fidelity-provided information and information from third-party data sources and providers and therefore Fidelity cannot make any representations or guarantees as to its timeliness and accuracy. Fidelity will not provide notification that past data may have been inaccurate, or that it has been corrected.</p>
						<p>Personal Rate of Return (money-weighted) information may not be available for the following account types: Employer-Sponsored Retirement Plans (e.g., 401(k) plans), Brokerage Link accounts, Brokerage Flex accounts, certain insurance/annuity holdings, and stock plans. These accounts are also not included in the Rate of Return calculation for your entire portfolio appearing at the top of the Portfolio Summary page. Time-weighted returns are available for Employer-Sponsored Retirement Plans as of the end of the previous business day and can be accessed by See YTD Change link.</p>
						<p>Performance calculations include accounts that have been "hidden" since the last performance reporting period. "Hidden" accounts will be removed from all performance calculations during the next monthly update.</p>
						<p>Returns shown for periods that include company stock plan transactions typically start at the time of purchase, exercise or vesting. Please refer to Help/Glossary for more information.</p>
						<p>Your statement is the official record of holdings and transactions in your account. The money weighted returns shown here may use transaction data differently, and therefore, may be different from your statement.</p>

					<div id="legal-footer--today-change" class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" style="display: none;">
						<p>Today's Gain/Loss equals the total dollar change in securities held for the selected accounts identified in the account selector. This balance only factors in securities held and does not include any pending activity (debits/credits) within the selected accounts. The percentage change represents the total dollar change compared to the value of securities held in your accounts, not the total account value.</p>
						<p>Today's Gain/Loss does not include 529 CIT accounts, Annuity contracts, non-Fidelity accounts, workplace accounts or pension benefits listed in the All Accounts view.</p>
						<p>For securities priced daily, such as mutual funds, Today's Gain/Loss is calculated using the prior business day's market closing price. For securities priced intraday, Today's Gain/Loss is calculated using the last available price.</p>
						
					</div>
					<div id="legal-footer--balance-overtime" class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" style="display: none;">
						<p>Your Balance Over Time reflects the difference in your All Accounts total balance over the selected time period. It includes all gain, loss, deposit and withdrawal activity over the selected time period, as of the most recent market close. This difference is divided by the beginning total balance at the start of the selected time period to calculate the relevant percentage increase or decrease during this time period.</p>
						<p>All Accounts equals the sum of the balances of the selected accounts identified in the account selector. These accounts may include your Fidelity personal and workplace accounts, accounts managed by a third party adviser but held at Fidelity, and accounts accessible via the Full View service (identified as non-Fidelity accounts, if you have signed up for this service). Information regarding non-Fidelity accounts that are denominated in foreign currency or that hold positions in foreign currency may be displayed on this page in USD. You may view information for non-Fidelity accounts in its original foreign denomination using the FullView service. Fidelity is not able to verify the accuracy, timeliness or completeness of information regarding accounts accessible via the Full View service.</p>
						<p>This information is provided as a convenience and is not a substitute for your Fidelity account statement, nor is it intended for trading purposes. Please consult your account statement, and any statements from the respective financial institution for the accounts provided for information regarding your account balance, positions, and transactions. This information may include assets that Fidelity does not hold on your behalf and which are obtained through the Full View service.</p>
					</div>
					<div id="legal-footer--gps" class="legal-footer--item-content-detail" style="display: none;">
						<p>Your Allocation Style is determined based on the rounded percentage of <b>equity holdings</b> in your selected accounts as follows:
						</p><ul class="legal-list">
							<li>if equity % is less than or equal to 10%, then Short Term;</li>
							<li>if equity % is between 11% - 24%, then Conservative;</li>
							<li>if equity % is between 25% - 34%, then Moderate With Income;</li>
							<li>if equity % is between 35% - 44%, then Moderate;</li> 
							<li>if equity % is between 45% - 54%, then Balanced;</li>
							<li>if equity % is between 55% - 64%, then Growth With Income;</li>
							<li>if equity % is between 65% - 78%, then Growth;</li>
							<li>if equity % is between 79% - 92%, then Aggressive Growth;</li>
							<li>if equity % is greater than or equal to 93% then Most Aggressive;</li>
						</ul>
						<p>If a large portion of your holdings are identified as Unknown or Other, the percentage of equity holdings in your selected accounts may be low, indicating a low level of risk associated with your portfolio, without consideration of the risks associated with the Unknown and Other assets. If holdings data is not available to Fidelity, the interest is categorized as Unknown. The Other category includes non -asset class holdings (i.e., identified holdings that cannot be categorized as stocks, bonds or short-term investments). For additional details, please refer to the <a class="link-glossary" href="javascript:void(0);">Glossary of Terms</a>.</p>

During market open, mutual fund positions are priced as of the previous day's market close.</p>

						<p>Fidelity will attempt to cancel an open or partially filled order on
						a "best efforts" basis. Because Fidelity is responsible for
						executing an order as promptly as possible upon receipt, your order may
						have been partially or completely filled before the cancellation was
						received and accepted.</p>
						<p>A single order for a large quantity of shares of a security may be
						filled through multiple executions. In some cases, not all of these
						executions are accessible on this page. To verify if the order has been
						filled in its entirety, please go to the "Positions" page or call a
						trading representative at 1-800-544-6666.</p>
						
						<p>Price improvement details provided for domestic stock and single leg option orders entered during market hours after the primary opening, provided there is a National Best Bid and Offer (NBBO) at the time the order is placed. Price improvement details are provided for informational purposes only and are not used for regulatory reporting purposes.</p> 

						<p>Buy market orders with a weighted average <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://scs.fidelity.com/webxpress/help/topics/help_definition_e.shtml#executionprice')">execution price</a> below the National Best Offer (NBO) are considered price improved. Price improvement for buy market orders is calculated by subtracting the weighted average execution price from the NBO, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on buy limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the NBO minus the execution price and the limit price minus the execution price. Sell market orders with a weighted average execution price above the National Best Bid (NBB) are considered price improved. Price improvement for sell market orders is calculated by subtracting the NBB from the weighted average execution price, then multiplying by the number of executed shares to arrive at the net price improvement for the order. Price improvement on sell limit orders is calculated as the lesser of the execution price minus the NBB and the execution price minus the limit price.</p> 
						
						<p>Prior to December 7, 2015, price improvement for limit orders (buy and sell) was calculated using the methodology for price improvement on market orders described above.</p>
						
						<p>For buys and sells, price improvement is displayed per execution and per order, only when an order has been net price improved. Price improvements at the execution and individual order level are rounded down to the nearest penny.</p>
							
						<p>Price improvement data is not provided for not held orders, all or none orders, sell short orders, and orders placed outside of standard market hours.</p>
							
						<p>Some orders may not receive any price improvement. Fast market conditions and large order sizes relative to the bid or ask size may result in shares executing at or outside the NBBO. To learn more about our commitment to execution quality, click <a href="javascript:popLargerWin('https://www.fidelity.com/trading/execution-quality/overview')">here.</a></p>
